verbose_text: Relative to patients with moderately-severe AP, calcium levels were significantly higher and total bilirubin and glucose were lower in patients with mild AP (2.09 +/- 0.25 versus 1.92 +/- 0.32 mmol/l; 21.40 +/- 19.49 versus 32.41 +/- 15.38 mumol/l; 11.42 +/- 5.13 versus 14.01 +/- 5.13 mmol/l, respectively; all P < 0.05).
